actions.text: House Committee on Rules Reported an Original Measure. Report No: 99-608.
Called up by House as Privileged Matter.
Resolution Agreed to in House by Voice Vote.

official_title: A resolution waiving certain points of order against the conference report on (H. R. 2672) to redesignate the New York International and Bulk Mail Center in Jersey City, New Jersey, as the "New Jersey International and Bulk Mail Center", and to honor the memory of a former postal employee by dedicating a portion of a street at the New York International and Bulk Mail Center in Jersey City, New Jersey, as "Michael McDermott Place," and against the consideration of such conference report.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on H.R. 2672 (Federal employee retirement).
